			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The TIA implements the ÷15 as a series of carefully-tuned analog delays from the original NTSC colorburst frequency crystal. When it came to the PAL revision, they gave up retuning the inverters and only gave you 12 angles instead.<br /><br />It's much harder to move analog designs from one IC fabrication facility to another; often every carefully-tuned R and C need to be revisited when you do so. A purely-digital design, or at least one where the only values that matters is the ratios of specific resistors relative to each other (such as the 2A03's DACs), means it's a lot easier to move fabs as demand changes.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

